column2: #oneway anova, taking the mean count for each animal across all slides/positions

The ANOVA (formula: mean_count ~ AgeCat) suggests that:

  - The main effect of AgeCat is statistically significant and large (F(4, 15) = 13.51, p < .001; Eta2 = 0.78, 95% CI [0.54,
1.00])

Effect sizes were labelled following Field's (2013) recommendations.
